However, based on everything you've shared, the root cause is very likely:

RHEL 9.7 kernel: 5.14.0-611.26.1.el9_7.x86_64

VirtualBox: 6.1.50 (released years ago and now end-of-life)


VirtualBox 6.1.50 is not compatible with the latest RHEL 9.7 kernels.

Find the exact error

Run:

grep -n "error:" /var/log/vbox-setup.log | tail -20

or

grep -n "fatal" /var/log/vbox-setup.log

These commands will show the real compilation failure.

My recommendation

If you are free to upgrade, remove VirtualBox 6.1 and install VirtualBox 7.1.x, which supports newer kernels.

If you must stay on 6.1.50, your options are limited:

Boot an older kernel that VirtualBox 6.1 supports, or

Apply unofficial patches to the VirtualBox source (not recommended).


